Class MsdxContainer<T>

java.lang.Object
io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.MsdxContainer<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
MsdxRecord
public class MsdxContainer<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
The class holds heterogeneous objects and serves a fundamental role as general purpose data carriers that are used the bridging stream operations for creating solver-specific modeling objects. This class provides uniformity in handling those streams while avoiding creating many context-specific classes. Container is used in Record, Schema, Instance, Dataframe and Span.

This class is designed to handle either data as a Record, having a prespecified schema, or a Schema itself. For data, use the type parameter T= Object; for a schema, use the type parameter T= Class<?>.
